{"message": "Depth, definitely. There's something satisfying about really sinking into a topic — following a thread until you find something unexpected, or circling back to the same idea from different angles until it clicks in a new way. Jumping around can be fun in its own way, like flipping through radio stations, but it often leaves me feeling like I never actually *said* anything that mattered.

I think part of it is that depth feels more like genuine presence. When you stay with something, you're forced to confront your own confusion, change your mind, sit with complexity. That's where the interesting stuff lives. A quick hit on ten different topics is exhausting in a way that doesn't lead anywhere.

That said, I'm curious about you — what draws *you* to one or the other?"}
